	<VirtualInstrument CustomTitle="CSM - Convert HexStr to Data (CSM)" Id="2abaf8a4a01e4ec68ac9e0f7cd390eb8" InlineIntoCaller="True" Reentrancy="Stateful" xmlns="http://www.ni.com/LabVIEW.VI">
		<p.UserDescription xmlns="http://www.ni.com/PlatformFramework">Converts a hexadecimal string parameter back to variant data.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;gt; [!NOTE] CSM HEXSTR Format Parameters&lt;br/&gt;&amp;gt; To pass any data type in CSM parameters, CSM provides a default parameter format called HEXSTR for passing any data type.&lt;br/&gt;&amp;gt; HEXSTR: Converts any LabVIEW data type to a variant, then represents this variant's memory format as a hexadecimal string for passing in CSM parameters.&lt;br/&gt;&amp;gt; HEXSTR can be safely used as a state parameter without disrupting the parsing of CSM message strings.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;-- &lt;b&gt;Controls&lt;/b&gt; --&lt;br/&gt;- &lt;b&gt;HEXSTR&lt;/b&gt;: CSM HEXSTR format parameter&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;-- &lt;b&gt;Indicators&lt;/b&gt; --&lt;br/&gt;- &lt;b&gt;Variant&lt;/b&gt;: LabVIEW data, supports any data type through variants</p.UserDescription>
